  <prompt>
    Add an optional `string? SearchIndexName { get; init; }` property to the three request DTOs: `SemanticSearchRequest`, `RagSearchRequest`, `RecordSearchRequest`. JSON deserialization MUST be forward-compatible — requests WITHOUT this field continue to parse and work as today (NFR-02).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    BFF developer familiar with `Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/`. Read `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` for the binding pre-merge checklist before editing.
  </role>

  <goal>
    All three request DTOs expose `SearchIndexName` (nullable, init-only). Existing serialization tests pass unmodified. New requests with `searchIndexName` deserialize correctly; old requests without it deserialize with `SearchIndexName = null`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Phase B threads an explicit index identifier from client to resolver. Task 010 extended the resolver signature; this task adds the DTO surface so the endpoint layer can read `request.SearchIndexName` and pass it to the resolver. Forward-compat is mandatory — existing PCF + code-page callers must continue to work.
    </background>
